#: en/book/ch03-advanced-topics.xml:1007
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"All of this property adding and editing isn't really very useful if you "
"can't easily get the stored property value.  So the <command>svn</command> "
"program supplies two subcommands for displaying the names and values of "
"properties stored on files and directories.  The <command>svn proplist</"
"command> command will list the names of properties that exist on a path.  "
"Once you know the names of the properties on the node, you can request their "
"values individually using <command>svn propget</command>.  This command "
"will, given a property name and a path (or set of paths), print the value of "
"the property to the standard output stream."
