#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5640
msgid ""
"If you're currently inside the directory <filename>vendors</filename>, which "
"was branched to <filename>vendors-with-fix</filename>, and you'd like to "
"switch your working copy to that branch:"
msgstr ""
"<filename>vendors-with-fix</filename> から分岐した <filename>vendors</"
"filename> というディレクトリ内にいて、そのブランチの作業コピーに移りたい場合"
"は以下のようにします。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5647
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn switch http://svn.red-bean.com/repos/branches/vendors-with-fix .\n"
"U    myproj/foo.txt\n"
"U    myproj/bar.txt\n"
"U    myproj/baz.c\n"
"U    myproj/qux.c\n"
"Updated to revision 31.\n"
msgstr ""
"$ svn switch http://svn.red-bean.com/repos/branches/vendors-with-fix .\n"
"U    myproj/foo.txt\n"
"U    myproj/bar.txt\n"
"U    myproj/baz.c\n"
"U    myproj/qux.c\n"
"リビジョン 31 に更新しました。\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5656
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"To switch back, just provide the URL to the location in the repository from "
"which you originally checked out your working copy:"
msgstr ""
"そして、元に戻りたいときには、最初に作業コピーをチェックアウトしたリポジト"
"リーの場所を、URL として指定するだけです。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5662
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn switch http://svn.red-bean.com/repos/trunk/vendors .\n"
"U    myproj/foo.txt\n"
"U    myproj/bar.txt\n"
"U    myproj/baz.c\n"
"U    myproj/qux.c\n"
"Updated to revision 31.\n"
msgstr ""
"$ svn switch http://svn.red-bean.com/repos/trunk/vendors .\n"
"U    myproj/foo.txt\n"
"U    myproj/bar.txt\n"
"U    myproj/baz.c\n"
"U    myproj/qux.c\n"
"リビジョン 31 に更新しました。\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><tip><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5672
msgid ""
"You <emphasis>can</emphasis> switch just part of your working copy to a "
"branch if you don't want to switch your entire working copy, but this is not "
"generally recommended.  It's too easy to forget that you've done this and "
"wind up accidentally making and committing changes both to the switched and "
"unswitched portions of your tree."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><indexterm><tertiary>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5691
msgid "unlock"
msgstr "unlock"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refnamediv><refname>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5695
msgid "svn unlock"
msgstr "svn unlock"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refnamediv><refpurpose>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5696
msgid "Unlock working copy paths or URLs."
msgstr "作業コピーパスや URL をロック解除します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5700
msgid "<literal>svn unlock TARGET...</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn unlock TARGET...</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5705
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Unlock each <replaceable>TARGET</replaceable>.  If any <replaceable>TARGET</"
"replaceable> is locked by another user or no valid lock token exists in the "
"working copy, print a warning and continue unlocking the rest of the "
"<replaceable>TARGET</replaceable>s.  Use <option>--force</option> to break a "
"lock belonging to another user or working copy."
msgstr ""
"<replaceable>TARGET</replaceable> のロックをそれぞれ解除します。 "
"<replaceable>TARGET</replaceable> が他のユーザによってロックされていたり、作"
"業コピー中に有効なロックトークンが存在しない場合、警告を出力して残りの "
"<replaceable>TARGET</replaceable> のロック解除を続けます。他のユーザや作業コ"
"ピーに属するロックを破壊するには、<option>--force</option> を使用してくださ"
"い。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5720
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"--force\n"
"--targets FILENAME\n"
msgstr ""
"--force\n"
"--targets FILENAME\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5729
msgid "Unlock two files in your working copy:"
msgstr "作業コピーにある二つのファイルロックを解除します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5733
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn unlock tree.jpg house.jpg\n"
"'tree.jpg' unlocked.\n"
"'house.jpg' unlocked.\n"
msgstr ""
"$ svn unlock tree.jpg house.jpg\n"
"'tree.jpg' のロックは解除されました。\n"
"'house.jpg' のロックは解除されました。\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5739
msgid ""
"Unlock a file in your working copy that is currently locked by another user:"
msgstr ""
"現在別のユーザがロックしている作業コピー内のファイルをロック解除します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5744
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn unlock tree.jpg\n"
"svn: E195013: 'tree.jpg' is not locked in this working copy\n"
"$ svn unlock --force tree.jpg\n"
"'tree.jpg' unlocked.\n"
msgstr ""
"$ svn unlock tree.jpg\n"
"svn: E195013: 'tree.jpg' はこの作業コピーでロックされていません\n"
"$ svn unlock --force tree.jpg\n"
"'tree.jpg' のロックは解除されました。\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5751
msgid "Unlock a file without a working copy:"
msgstr "作業コピーにないファイルをロック解除します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5755
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn unlock http://svn.red-bean.com/repos/test/tree.jpg\n"
"'tree.jpg unlocked.\n"
msgstr ""
"$ svn unlock http://svn.red-bean.com/repos/test/tree.jpg\n"
"'tree.jpg のロックは解除されました。\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refnamediv><refname>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5777
msgid "svn update (up)"
msgstr "svn update (up)"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refnamediv><refpurpose>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5778
msgid "Update your working copy."
msgstr "作業コピーを更新します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5782
msgid "<literal>svn update [PATH...]</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn update [PATH...]</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5787
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<command>svn update</command> brings changes from the repository into your "
"working copy.  If no revision is given, it brings your working copy up to "
"date with the <literal>HEAD</literal> revision.  Otherwise, it synchronizes "
"the working copy to the revision given by the <option>--revision</option> "
"(<option>-r</option>) option.  As part of the synchronization, <command>svn "
"update</command> also removes any stale locks (see <xref linkend=\"svn.tour."
"cleanup\"/>) found in the working copy."
msgstr ""
"<command>svn update</command> は、リポジトリーにある変更を作業コピーに反映し"
"ます。リビジョンを指定しなければ、<literal>HEAD</literal> リビジョンの最新の"
"内容を反映します。そうでなければ、<option>--revision</option> オプションで指"
"定したリビジョンに、作業コピーを同期します。同期処理の一部として、"
"<command>svn update</command> は作業コピーに存在する古いロックを削除します "
"(<xref linkend=\"svn.tour.cleanup\"/> をご覧ください)。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5798
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"For each updated item, it prints a line that starts with a character "
"reporting the action taken.  These characters have the following meaning:"
msgstr ""
"更新される項目ごとに、どのような動作を起こしたかを示す文字で始まる行を出力し"
"ます。この文字は以下のような意味になります。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5812
msgid "<literal>B</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>B</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5814
msgid "Broken lock (third column only)"
msgstr "壊れたロック (3 列目のみ)"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5847
msgid "<literal>E</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>E</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5849
msgid "Existed"
msgstr "既存"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5855
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A character in the first column signifies an update to the actual file, "
"whereas updates to the file's properties are shown in the second column.  "
"Lock information is printed in the third column."
msgstr ""
"1 列目の文字は実際のファイルの更新を示し、ファイルの属性の更新状況は 2 列目で"
"示します。ロック情報は 3 列目に出力します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5860
msgid ""
"As with most subcommands, you can limit the scope of the update operation to "
"a particular tree depth using the <option>--depth</option> option.  "
"Alternatively, you can use the <option>--set-depth</option> option to set a "
"new <quote>sticky</quote> working copy depth on the update target."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5873
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"--accept ACTION\n"
"--changelist\n"
"--depth ARG\n"
"--diff3-cmd CMD\n"
"--editor-cmd CMD\n"
"--force\n"
"--ignore-externals\n"
"--parents\n"
"--quiet (-q)\n"
"--revision (-r) REV\n"
"--set-depth ARG\n"
msgstr ""
"--accept ACTION\n"
"--changelist\n"
"--depth ARG\n"
"--diff3-cmd CMD\n"
"--editor-cmd CMD\n"
"--force\n"
"--ignore-externals\n"
"--parents\n"
"--quiet (-q)\n"
"--revision (-r) REV\n"
"--set-depth ARG\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5891
msgid "Pick up repository changes that have happened since your last update:"
msgstr "最後の更新後に起きた、リポジトリーへの更新を取り込みます。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5896
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn update\n"
"Updating '.':\n"
"A    newdir/toggle.c\n"
"A    newdir/disclose.c\n"
"A    newdir/launch.c\n"
"D    newdir/README\n"
"Updated to revision 32.\n"
msgstr ""
"$ svn update\n"
"Updating '.':\n"
"A    newdir/toggle.c\n"
"A    newdir/disclose.c\n"
"A    newdir/launch.c\n"
"D    newdir/README\n"
"リビジョン 32 に更新しました。\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5906
msgid ""
"You can also <quote>update</quote> your working copy to an older revision "
"(Subversion doesn't have the concept of <quote>sticky</quote> files like CVS "
"does; see <xref linkend=\"svn.forcvs\"/>):"
msgstr ""
"もっと古いリビジョンで作業コピーを更新することもできます。(Subversion は CVS "
"のような <quote>張り付き</quote> ファイルの概念を持ちません。 <xref linkend="
"\"svn.forcvs\"/> をご覧ください):"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5913
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn update -r30\n"
"Updating '.':\n"
"A    newdir/README\n"
"D    newdir/toggle.c\n"
"D    newdir/disclose.c\n"
"D    newdir/launch.c\n"
"U    foo.c\n"
"Updated to revision 30.\n"
msgstr ""
"$ svn update -r30\n"
"Updating '.':\n"
"A    newdir/README\n"
"D    newdir/toggle.c\n"
"D    newdir/disclose.c\n"
"D    newdir/launch.c\n"
"U    foo.c\n"
"リビジョン 30 に更新しました。\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><tip><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5925
msgid ""
"If you want to examine an older revision of a single file, you may want to "
"use <command>svn cat</command> instead&mdash;it won't change your working "
"copy."
msgstr ""
"ひとつのファイルの古いバージョンを調べる際には、作業コピーの更新を行わない "
"<command>svn cat</command> を使う方がいいかもしれません。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5931
msgid ""
"<command>svn update</command> is also the primary mechanism used to "
"configure sparse working copies.  When used with the <option>--set-depth</"
"option>, the update operation will omit or reenlist individual working copy "
"members by modifying their recorded ambient depth to the depth you specify "
"(fetching information from the repository as necessary).  See <xref linkend="
"\"svn.advanced.sparsedirs\" /> for more about sparse directories."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5941
msgid ""
"You can update multiple targets with a single invocation, and Subversion "
"will not only gracefully skip any unversioned targets you provide it, but as "
"of Subversion 1.7 will also include a post-update summary of all the updates "
"it performed:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5949
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd my-projects\n"
"$ svn update *\n"
"Updating 'calc':\n"
"U    button.c\n"
"U    integer.c\n"
"Updated to revision 394.\n"
"Skipped 'tempfile.tmp'\n"
"Updating 'paint':\n"
"A    palettes.c\n"
"U    brushes.c\n"
"Updated to revision 60.\n"
"Updating 'ziptastic':\n"
"At revision 43.\n"
"Summary of updates:\n"
"  Updated 'calc' to r394.\n"
"  Updated 'paint' to r60.\n"
"  Updated 'ziptastic' to r43.\n"
"Summary of conflicts:\n"
"  Skipped paths: 1\n"
"$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><indexterm><tertiary>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5981 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:7375
msgid "upgrade"
msgstr "upgrade"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refnamediv><refname>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5985
msgid "svn upgrade"
msgstr "svn upgrade"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refnamediv><refpurpose>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5986
msgid "Upgrade the metadata storage format for a working copy."
msgstr "作業コピーのメタデータストレージフォーマットのアップグレード"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5991
msgid "<literal>svn upgrade [PATH...]</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn upgrade [PATH...]</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:5996
msgid ""
"As new versions of Subversion are released, the format used for the working "
"copy metadata changes to accomodate new features or fix bugs.  Older "
"versions of Subversion would automatically upgrade working copies to the new "
"format the first time the working copy was used by the new version of the "
"software.  Beginning with Subversion 1.7, working copy upgrades must be "
"explicitly performed at the user's request.  <command>svn upgrade</command> "
"is the subcommand used to trigger that upgrade process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6012 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:7153
#, no-wrap
msgid "--quiet (-q)\n"
msgstr "--quiet (-q)\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6020
msgid ""
"If you attempt to use Subversion 1.7 on a working copy created with an older "
"version of Subversion, you will see an error:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6026
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn status\n"
"svn: E155036: Please see the 'svn upgrade' command\n"
"svn: E155036: Working copy '/home/sally/project' is too old (format 10, create\n"
"d by Subversion 1.6)\n"
"$\n"
msgstr ""
"$ svn status\n"
"svn: E155036: Please see the 'svn upgrade' command\n"
"svn: E155036: Working copy '/home/sally/project' is too old (format 10, create\n"
"d by Subversion 1.6)\n"
"$\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6034
msgid ""
"Use the <command>svn upgrade</command> command to upgrade the working copy "
"to the most recent metadata format supported by your version of Subversion."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6040
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn upgrade\n"
"Upgraded '.'\n"
"Upgraded 'A'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/B'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/B/E'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/B/F'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/C'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/D'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/D/G'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/D/H'\n"
"$ svn status\n"
"D       A/B/E/alpha\n"
"M       A/D/gamma\n"
"A       A/newfile\n"
"$\n"
msgstr ""
"$ svn upgrade\n"
"Upgraded '.'\n"
"Upgraded 'A'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/B'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/B/E'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/B/F'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/C'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/D'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/D/G'\n"
"Upgraded 'A/D/H'\n"
"$ svn status\n"
"D       A/B/E/alpha\n"
"M       A/D/gamma\n"
"A       A/newfile\n"
"$\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6058
msgid ""
"Notice that <command>svn upgrade</command> preserved the local modifications "
"present in the working copy at the time of the upgrade, which were "
"introduced by the version of Subversion previously used to manipulate this "
"working copy."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><warning><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6065
msgid ""
"As was the case with automatically upgraded working copies in the past, "
"explicitly upgraded working copies will be unusable by older versions of "
"Subversion, too."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6081
msgid "svnadmin&mdash;Subversion Repository Administration"
msgstr "svnadmin&mdash;Subversion リポジトリーの管理"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6083
msgid ""
"<command>svnadmin</command> is the administrative tool for monitoring and "
"repairing your Subversion repository.  For detailed information on "
"repository administration, see the maintenance section for <xref linkend="
"\"svn.reposadmin.maint.tk.svnadmin\"/>."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnadmin</command> は、Subversion リポジトリーを監視したり修復したり"
"するための管理ツールです。リポジトリー管理についての詳細は、<xref linkend="
"\"svn.reposadmin.maint.tk.svnadmin\"/> の保守セクションをご覧ください。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6088
msgid ""
"Since <command>svnadmin</command> works via direct repository access (and "
"thus can only be used on the machine that holds the repository), it refers "
"to the repository with a path, not a URL."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnadmin</command> は、直接リポジトリーにアクセス (し、ポジトリが存"
"在するマシン上でのみ利用) して動作するため、URL ではなく、パスによってリポジ"
"トリーを参照します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6094
msgid "svnadmin Options"
msgstr "svnadmin のオプション"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6096
msgid ""
"Options in <command>svnadmin</command> are global, just as they are in "
"<command>svn</command>:"
msgstr ""
"<command>svmadin</command> のオプションは、<command>svn</command> のものと同"
"様、グローバルです。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6102
msgid "<option>--bdb-log-keep</option>"
msgstr "<option>--bdb-log-keep</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6104
msgid ""
"(Berkeley DB-specific.) Disable automatic log removal of database logfiles.  "
"Having these logfiles around can be convenient if you need to restore from a "
"catastrophic repository failure."
msgstr ""
"(Berkeley DB 固有) データベースログファイルの、自動ログ削除機能を無効にしま"
"す。このログを保持しておくと、壊滅的なリポジトリーエラーから回復する必要があ"
"るときに役に立ちます。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6112
msgid "<option>--bdb-txn-nosync</option>"
msgstr "<option>--bdb-txn-nosync</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6115
msgid ""
"(Berkeley DB-specific.) Disables fsync when committing database "
"transactions.  Used with the <command>svnadmin create</command> command to "
"create a Berkeley DB-backed repository with <literal>DB_TXN_NOSYNC</literal> "
"enabled (which improves speed but has some risks associated with it)."
msgstr ""
"(Berkeley DB 固有) データベーストランザクションをコミットする際の fsync を無"
"効にします。Berkeley DB バックエンドリポジトリーを <literal>DB_TXN_NOSYNC</"
"literal> を有効 (リスクと引き替えに速度を改善) にして作成するのに、"
"<command>svnadmin create</command> コマンドと一緒に使用してください。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6125
msgid "<option>--bypass-hooks</option>"
msgstr "<option>--bypass-hooks</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6127
msgid "Bypass the repository hook system."
msgstr "リポジトリーフックシステムを迂回します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6132
msgid "<option>--bypass-prop-validation</option>"
msgstr "<option>--bypass-prop-validation</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6134
msgid ""
"When loading a dump file, disable the logic which validates property values."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6140
msgid "<option>--clean-logs</option>"
msgstr "<option>--clean-logs</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6142
msgid "Remove unused Berkeley DB logs."
msgstr "利用していない Berkeley DB ログを削除します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6150 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9809
msgid ""
"<option>--memory-cache-size</option> (<option>-M</option>) <replaceable>ARG</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<option>--memory-cache-size</option> (<option>-M</option>) <replaceable>ARG</"
"replaceable>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6153 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9812
msgid ""
"Configures the size (in Megabytes) of the extra in-memory cache used to "
"minimize redundant operations.  The default value is <literal>16</literal>.  "
"(This cache is used for FSFS-backed repositories only.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6161
msgid "<option>--force-uuid</option>"
msgstr "<option>--force-uuid</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6163
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"By default, when loading data into a repository that already contains "
"revisions, <command>svnadmin</command> will ignore the UUID from the dump "
"stream.  This option will cause the repository's UUID to be set to the UUID "
"from the stream."
msgstr ""
"デフォルトでは、リポジトリーに対して既に存在しているリビジョンをロードする場"
"合、<command>svnadmin</command> はダンプストリームにある <literal>UUID</"
"literal> を無視します。このオプションはリポジトリーの <literal>UUID</"
"literal> をストリームからの <literal>UUID</literal> に設定します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6172
msgid "<option>--ignore-uuid</option>"
msgstr "<option>--ignore-uuid</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6174
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"By default, when loading data into an empty repository, <command>svnadmin</"
"command> will set the repository's UUID to the UUID from the dump stream.  "
"This option will cause the UUID from the stream to be ignored."
msgstr ""
"デフォルトでは、空のリポジトリーをロードする場合 <command>svnadmin</command> "
"はダンプストリームからの <literal>UUID</literal> を無視します。このオプション"
"は、UUID を無視するよう強制します (設定ファイルに <option>--force-uuid</"
"option> が設定されている場合、上書きするのに便利です)。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6184
msgid ""
"Dump a revision only as a diff against the previous revision, instead of the "
"usual fulltext."
msgstr ""
"リビジョンの全体をダンプするのではなく、以前のリビジョンに対する差分として ダ"
"ンプします。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6191
msgid "<option>--parent-dir <replaceable>DIR</replaceable></option>"
msgstr "<option>--parent-dir <replaceable>DIR</replaceable></option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6194
msgid ""
"When loading a dump file, root paths at <replaceable>DIR</replaceable> "
"instead of <filename>/</filename>."
msgstr ""
"ダンプファイルをロードするとき、ルートパスとして <filename>/</filename> のか"
"わりに <replaceable>DIR</replaceable> を使います。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6201
msgid "<option>--pre-1.4-compatible</option>"
msgstr "<option>--pre-1.4-compatible</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:6203
msgid ""
"When creating a new repository, use a format that is compatible with "
"versions of Subversion earlier than Subversion 1.4."
