#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9626
msgid ""
"Dump the contents of a local repository, and use <command>svnrdump load</"
"command> to transfer that revision information into an existing remote "
"repository:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><informalexample><screen>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9633
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svnadmin dump -q /var/svn/repos/new-project | \\\n"
"      svnrdump load http://svn.example.com/repos/new-project\n"
"* Loaded revision 0\n"
"* Loaded revision 1.\n"
"* Loaded revision 2.\n"
"&hellip;\n"
msgstr ""
"$ svnadmin dump -q /var/svn/repos/new-project | \\\n"
"      svnrdump load http://svn.example.com/repos/new-project\n"
"* Loaded revision 0\n"
"* Loaded revision 1.\n"
"* Loaded revision 2.\n"
"&hellip;\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><refentry><refsect1><note><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9643
msgid ""
"To operate properly <command>svnrdump load</command> requires that the "
"target repository have revision property modification enabled via the pre-"
"revprop-change hook.  For details about that hook, see <xref linkend=\"svn."
"ref.reposhooks.pre-revprop-change\" />."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9661
msgid "svnserve&mdash;Custom Subversion Server"
msgstr "svnserve&mdash;カスタム Subversion サーバー"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9663
msgid ""
"<command>svnserve</command> allows access to Subversion repositories using "
"Subversion's custom network protocol."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnserve</command> を使用すると、Subversion のカスタムネットワークプ"
"ロトコルで Subversion リポジトリーにアクセスできます。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9666
msgid ""
"You can run <command>svnserve</command> as a standalone server process (for "
"clients that are using the <literal>svn://</literal> access method); you can "
"have a daemon such as <command>inetd</command> or <command>xinetd</command> "
"launch it for you on demand (also for <literal>svn://</literal>), or you can "
"have <command>sshd</command> launch it on demand for the <literal>svn+ssh://"
"</literal> access method."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnserve</command> を、スタンドアロンサーバープロセス (クライアント"
"は <literal>svn://</literal> アクセス方法を利用)で実行する、<command>inetd</"
"command> や <command>xinetd</command> のようなデーモンで必要に応じて起動 (こ"
"れも <literal>svn://</literal>) する、<command>sshd</command> があれば "
"<literal>svn+ssh://</literal> アクセス方法で必要に応じて起動すると言った方法"
"で実行できます。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9675
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Regardless of the access method, once the client has selected a repository "
"by transmitting its URL, <command>svnserve</command> reads a file named "
"<filename>conf/svnserve.conf</filename> in the repository directory to "
"determine repository-specific settings such as what authentication database "
"to use and what authorization policies to apply.  See <xref linkend=\"svn."
"serverconfig.svnserve\"/> for details of the <filename>svnserve.conf</"
"filename> file."
msgstr ""
"アクセス方法によらず、クライアントが URL を送ってリポジトリーを選択すると、"
"<command>svnserve</command> はリポジトリーディレクトリにある <filename>conf/"
"svnserve.conf</filename> という名前のファイルを読んで、どのような認証用データ"
"ベースを使い、またどのような認証方法を使うかといった設定を、リポジトリーごと"
"に決めます。<filename>svnserve.conf</filename> ファイルの詳細は <xref "
"linkend=\"svn.serverconfig.svnserve\"/> をご覧ください。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9687
msgid "svnserve Options"
msgstr "svnserve のオプション"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9689
msgid ""
"Unlike the previous commands we've described, <command>svnserve</command> "
"has no subcommands&mdash;it is controlled exclusively by options."
msgstr ""
"すでに説明してきたコマンドとは違い、<command>svnserve</command> にはサブコマ"
"ンドがありません &mdash; <command>svnserve</command> はオプションにより排他的"
"に制御されます。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9697
msgid "<option>--cache-fulltexts</option> <replaceable>ARG</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>--cache-fulltexts</option> <replaceable>ARG</replaceable>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9700
msgid ""
"Toggles support for fulltext file content caching (in FSFS repositories "
"only)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9706
msgid "<option>--cache-txdeltas</option> <replaceable>ARG</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>--cache-txdeltas</option> <replaceable>ARG</replaceable>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9709
msgid ""
"Toggles support for file content delta caching (in FSFS repositories only)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9715
msgid "<option>--compression</option> <replaceable>LEVEL</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>--compression</option> <replaceable>LEVEL</replaceable>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9718
msgid ""
"Specifies the level of compression used for wire transmissions as an integer "
"beween 0 and 9, inclusive.  A value of <literal>9</literal> offers the best "
"compression, <literal>5</literal> is the default value, and <literal>0</"
"literal> disables compression altogether."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9728
msgid "<option>--daemon</option> (<option>-d</option>)"
msgstr "<option>--daemon</option> (<option>-d</option>)"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9730
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to run in daemon mode.  "
"<command>svnserve</command> backgrounds itself and accepts and serves TCP/IP "
"connections on the <literal>svn</literal> port (3690, by default)."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnserve</command> をデーモンモードで実行します。<command>svnserve</"
"command> 自身はバックグラウンドで実行し、<literal>svn</literal> ポート (デ"
"フォルトは 3690) で TCP/IP 接続を受け付け、サービスを提供します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9739
msgid "<option>--foreground</option>"
msgstr "<option>--foreground</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9741
msgid ""
"When used together with <option>-d</option>, causes <command>svnserve</"
"command> to stay in the foreground.  This is mainly useful for debugging."
msgstr ""
"<option>-d</option> と一緒に利用すると、<command>svnserve</command> がフォア"
"グラウントで待機するようになります。このオプションは主にデバッグ時に便利で"
"す。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9748
msgid "<option>--inetd</option> (<option>-i</option>)"
msgstr "<option>--inetd</option> (<option>-i</option>)"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9750
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to use the <filename>stdin</filename> and "
"<filename>stdout</filename> file descriptors, as is appropriate for a daemon "
"running out of <command>inetd</command>."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnserve</command> が<filename>stdin</filename> と "
"<filename>stdout</filename> のファイルディスクリプタを利用するように指定しま"
"す。<command>inetd</command> と共に利用する場合に適しています。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9757 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10354
msgid "<option>--help</option> (<option>-h</option>)"
msgstr "<option>--help</option> (<option>-h</option>)"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9759
msgid "Displays a usage summary and exits."
msgstr "使用方法の概要を表示し終了します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9764
msgid "<option>--listen-host</option> <replaceable>HOST</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>--listen-host</option> <replaceable>HOST</replaceable>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9767
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to listen on the interface specified by "
"<replaceable>HOST</replaceable>, which may be either a hostname or an IP "
"address."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnserve</command> が <replaceable>HOST</replaceable> で指定したイン"
"ターフェース上で待ち受けるようにします。ホスト名か IP アドレスの いずれかで指"
"定します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9774
msgid "<option>--listen-once</option> (<option>-X</option>)"
msgstr "<option>--listen-once</option> (<option>-X</option>)"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9776
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to accept one connection on the "
"<literal>svn</literal> port, serve it, and exit.  This option is mainly "
"useful for debugging."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnserve</command> は、<literal>svn</literal> ポート上でひとつだけ接"
"続を受け入れ、サービス提供後終了します。このオプションは主にデバッグ時に便利"
"です。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9784
msgid "<option>--listen-port</option> <replaceable>PORT</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>--listen-port</option> <replaceable>PORT</replaceable>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9787
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to listen on <replaceable>PORT</"
"replaceable> when run in daemon mode.  (FreeBSD daemons listen only on tcp6 "
"by default&mdash;this option tells them to also listen on tcp4.)"
msgstr ""
"デーモンモードで実行時に、<replaceable>PORT</replaceable> で待ち受けるように "
"<command>svnserve</command> に指定します。(FreeBSD のデーモンは、デフォルト"
"で tcp6 でのみ待ち受けします &mdash; これにより tcp4 でも待ち受けするようにな"
"ります)"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9795
msgid "<option>--log-file</option> <replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>--log-file</option> <replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9798
msgid ""
"Instructs <command>svnserve</command> to create (if necessary) and use the "
"file located at <replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable> for Subversion "
"operational log output of the same sort that <command>mod_dav_svn</command> "
"generates.  See <xref linkend=\"svn.serverconfig.operational-logging\" /> "
"for details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9820
msgid "<option>--pid-file</option> <replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>--pid-file</option> <replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9823
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to write its process ID to "
"<replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable>, which must be writable by the user "
"under which <command>svnserve</command> is running."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnserve</command> が、自分のプロセス ID を書き込むファイルを "
"<replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable> とします。このファイルは "
"<command>svnserve</command> の実行ユーザが書き込めなければなりません。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9831
msgid "<option>--prefer-ipv6</option> (<option>-6</option>"
msgstr "<option>--prefer-ipv6</option> (<option>-6</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9833
msgid ""
"When resolving the listen hostname, prever an IPv6 answer over an IPv4 one.  "
"IPv4 is preferred by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9840 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10008
msgid "<option>--quiet</option>"
msgstr "<option>--quiet</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9842
msgid "Disables progress notifications.  Error output will still be printed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9848
msgid ""
"<option>--root</option> (<option>-r</option>)  <replaceable>ROOT</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<option>--root</option> (<option>-r</option>)  <replaceable>ROOT</"
"replaceable>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9851
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Sets the virtual root for repositories served by <command>svnserve</"
"command>.  The pathname in URLs provided by the client will be interpreted "
"relative to this root and will not be allowed to escape this root."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnserve</command> によって提供されるリポジトリーの仮想ルートを設定"
"します。クライアントからの URL 中のパス名は、このルートからの相対パスと解釈さ"
"れ、その外側にアクセスすることを許しません。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9860
msgid "<option>--threads</option> (<option>-T</option>)"
msgstr "<option>--threads</option> (<option>-T</option>)"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9862
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"When running in daemon mode, causes <command>svnserve</command> to spawn a "
"thread instead of a process for each connection (e.g., for when running on "
"Windows).  The <command>svnserve</command> process still backgrounds itself "
"at startup time."
msgstr ""
"デーモンモードで実行する場合、<command>svnserve</command> が、接続ごとにプロ"
"セスを起動するのではなく、スレッドを起動するように指定します (Windows で実行"
"するときなど)。 <command>svnserve</command>自身は、やはり起動時にバックグラウ"
"ンドに常駐します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9871
msgid "<option>--tunnel</option> (<option>-t</option>)"
msgstr "<option>--tunnel</option> (<option>-t</option>)"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9873
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to run in tunnel mode, which is just like "
"the <command>inetd</command> mode of operation (both modes serve one "
"connection over <filename>stdin</filename>/<filename>stdout</filename>, and "
"then exit), except that the connection is considered to be preauthenticated "
"with the username of the current UID.  This flag is automatically passed for "
"you by the client when running over a tunnel agent such as <command>ssh</"
"command>.  That means there's rarely any need for <emphasis>you</emphasis> "
"to pass this option to <command>svnserve</command>.  So, if you find "
"yourself typing <literal>svnserve --tunnel</literal> on the command line and "
"wondering what to do next, see <xref linkend=\"svn.serverconfig.svnserve."
"sshauth\"/>."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnserve</command> がトンネルモードで実行するように指定します。"
"<command>inetd</command>と (標準入出力を使って接続するという意味で) 同様です"
"が、現在の uid に対応したユーザ名で、あらかじめ認証されているとみなします。こ"
"のフラグは <command>ssh</command>のような トンネルエージェント経由で実行する"
"際、クライアントによって自動的に渡されます。これは、<emphasis>あなた</"
"emphasis>がこのオプションを <command>svnserve</command> に渡す必要はまれにし"
"かないということです。ですから、コマンドラインに <literal>svnserve --tunnel</"
"literal> と入力して、次に何をしたらよいかわからなくなったら、<xref linkend="
"\"svn.serverconfig.svnserve.sshauth\"/> をご覧ください。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9892
msgid "<option>--tunnel-user NAME</option>"
msgstr "<option>--tunnel-user NAME</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9894
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Used in conjunction with the <option>--tunnel</option> option, tells "
"<command>svnserve</command> to assume that <replaceable>NAME</replaceable> "
"is the authenticated user, rather than the UID of the <command>svnserve</"
"command> process.  This is useful for users wishing to share a single system "
"account over SSH, but to maintain separate commit identities."
msgstr ""
"<option>--tunnel</option> オプションと一緒に使い、svnserve プロセスの UID の"
"かわりに <replaceable>NAME</replaceable> が認証されたユーザであると見なすよ"
"う、svnserve に指示します。SSH 経由では一つのシステムアカウントを共有しても、"
"コミットの主体は分けておきたいユーザに便利です。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9907
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Displays version information and a list of repository backend modules "
"available, and then exits."
msgstr ""
"バージョン情報と、利用可能なリポジトリーバックエンドモジュール一覧を表示して"
"終了します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9922
msgid "svndumpfilter&mdash;Subversion History Filtering"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9924
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<command>svndumpfilter</command> is a command-line utility for removing "
"history from a Subversion dump file by either excluding or including paths "
"beginning with one or more named prefixes.  For details, see <xref linkend="
"\"svn.reposadmin.maint.tk.svndumpfilter\"/>."
msgstr ""
"<command>svndumpfilter</command> は、Subversion のダンプファイルから、複数の"
"プレフィックスで始まる包含・除外パス指定により、履歴を削除するコマンドライン"
"ユーティリティです。詳細は、<xref linkend=\"svn.reposadmin.maint.tk."
"svndumpfilter\"/> をご覧ください。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9932
msgid "svndumpfilter Options"
msgstr "svndumpfilter のオプション"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9934
msgid ""
"Options in <command>svndumpfilter</command> are global, just as they are in "
"<command>svn</command> and <command>svnadmin</command>:"
msgstr ""
"<command>svndumpfilter</command> のオプションは、<command>svn</command> や "
"<command>svnadmin</command> と同様グローバルです。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9943
msgid ""
"If filtering causes any revision to be empty (i.e., causes no change to the "
"repository), removes these revisions from the final dump file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9950
msgid "<option>--pattern</option>"
msgstr "<option>--pattern</option>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9952
msgid ""
"Treat the path prefixes provided to the filtering commands as file glob "
"patterns rather than explicit path substrings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9961
msgid "Renumbers revisions that remain after filtering."
msgstr ""
"フィルタリングのあとで、残ったものに対して、リビジョン番号を付け直します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9967
msgid "<option>--skip-missing-merge-sources</option>"
msgstr "<option>--skip-missing-merge-sources</option>"

# type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9969
msgid ""
"Skips merge sources that have been removed as part of the filtering.  "
"Without this option, <command>svndumpfilter</command> will exit with an "
"error if the merge source for a retained path is removed by filtering."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9980
msgid ""
"If all nodes in a revision are removed by filtering and <option>--drop-empty-"
"revs</option> is not passed, the default behavior of <command>svndumpfilter</"
"command> is to remove all revision properties except for the date and the "
"log message (which will merely indicate that the revision is empty).  "
"Passing this option will preserve existing revision properties (which may or "
"may not make sense since the related content is no longer present in the "
"dump file)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:9996
msgid ""
"Instructs <command>svndumpfilter</command> to read additional path "
"prefixes&mdash;one per line&mdash;from the file located at "
"<replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable>.  This is especially useful for complex "
"filtering operations which require more prefixes than the operating system "
"allows to be specified on a single command line."
