#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10850
msgid "<literal>AuthzForceUsernameCase Upper|Lower</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>AuthzForceUsernameCase Upper|Lower</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10853
msgid ""
"Set to <literal>Upper</literal> or <literal>Lower</literal> to perform case "
"conversion of the specified sort on the authenticated username before "
"checking it for authorization.  While usernames are compared in a case-"
"sensitive fashion against those referenced in the authorization rules file, "
"this directive can at least normalize variably-cased usernames into "
"something consistent."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10866
msgid ""
"<literal>AuthzSVNAccessFile <replaceable>file-path</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""
"<literal>AuthzSVNAccessFile <replaceable>file-path</replaceable></literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10870
msgid ""
"Consult <replaceable>file-path</replaceable> for access rules describing the "
"permissions for paths in Subversion repository."
msgstr ""
"Subversion リポジトリーにあるパスのパーミッションについて、<replaceable>file-"
"path</replaceable> にアクセス規則を問い合わせます。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10878
msgid "<literal>AuthzSVNAnonymous On|Off</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>AuthzSVNAnonymous On|Off</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10881
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Set to <literal>Off</literal> to disable two special-case behaviours of this "
"module: interaction with the <literal>Satisfy Any</literal> directive and "
"enforcement of the authorization policy even when no <literal>Require</"
"literal> directives are present.  The default value of this directive is "
"<literal>On</literal>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>Off</literal> に設定すると、このモジュールのふたつの特殊な場合の挙動"
"を無効にします。これは、<literal>Satisfy Any</literal> ディレクティブとやりと"
"りすることと、<literal>Require</literal> ディレクティブが与えられていないとき"
"でさえ、認証ポリシーを強制することです。このディレクティブのデフォルト値は "
"<literal>On</literal> です。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10893
msgid "<literal>AuthzSVNAuthoritative On|Off</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>AuthzSVNAuthoritative On|Off</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10896
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Set to <literal>Off</literal> to allow access control to be passed along to "
"lower modules.  The default value of this directive is <literal>On</literal>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>Off</literal> に設定すると、下位のモジュールへアクセス制御を渡すよう"
"になります。このディレクティブのデフォルト値は <literal>On</literal> です。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10905
msgid "<literal>AuthzSVNNoAuthWhenAnonymousAllowed On|Off</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>AuthzSVNNoAuthWhenAnonymousAllowed On|Off</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10908
msgid ""
"Set to <literal>On</literal> to suppress authentication and authorization "
"for requests which anonymous users are allowed to perform.  The default "
"value of this directive is <literal>On</literal>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>On</literal> に設定すると、匿名ユーザの実行を許可し、認証認可の要求"
"を抑制します。このディレクティブのデフォルト値は <literal>On</literal> です。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10928
msgid "Subversion Properties"
msgstr "Subversion の属性"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10930
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Subversion allows users to invent arbitrarily named versioned properties on "
"files and directories, as well as unversioned properties on revisions.  The "
"only restriction is on properties whose names begin with <literal>svn:</"
"literal> (those are reserved for Subversion's own use).  While these "
"properties may be set by users to control Subversion's behavior, users may "
"not invent new <literal>svn:</literal> properties."
msgstr ""
"Subversion では、ファイルやディレクトリに対して、ユーザが任意の名前のバージョ"
"ン管理下の属性を設定でき、またリビジョンに対して、バージョン管理外の属性を設"
"定できます。名前が <literal>svn:</literal>で始まる属性にのみ、制限 "
"(Subversion が自分で使用するため予約) があります。Subversion の動作を制御する"
"ため、ユーザがこの属性を設定している場合、新しい <literal>svn:</literal> 属性"
"を設定できない可能性があります。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10940
msgid "Versioned Properties"
msgstr "バージョン管理下の属性"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10942
msgid ""
"These are the versioned properties that Subversion reserves for its own use:"
msgstr ""
"Subversion が使用するため予約している、バージョン管理下の属性は以下の通りで"
"す。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10948
msgid "<literal>svn:executable</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:executable</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10951
msgid ""
"If present on a file, the client will make the file executable in Unix-"
"hosted working copies.  See <xref linkend=\"svn.advanced.props.special."
"executable\"/>."
msgstr ""
"ファイルに設定すると、クライアントは Unix にある作業コピーのファイルを実行可"
"能にします。<xref linkend=\"svn.advanced.props.special.executable\"/> をご覧"
"ください。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10960
msgid "<literal>svn:mime-type</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:mime-type</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10963
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If present on a file, the value indicates the file's MIME type.  This allows "
"the client to decide whether line-based contextual merging is safe to "
"perform during updates, and can also affect how the file behaves when "
"fetched via a web browser.  See <xref linkend=\"svn.advanced.props.special."
"mime-type\"/>."
msgstr ""
"ファイルに設定すると、この値はファイルの MIME 型を表します。これによりクライ"
"アントは、更新時に行う行ベースの文脈マージが安全かどうか判断でき、Web ブラウ"
"ザで取得した際のファイルの扱い方も判断できます。<xref linkend=\"svn.advanced."
"props.special.mime-type\"/> をご覧ください。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10975
msgid "<literal>svn:ignore</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:ignore</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10978
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If present on a directory, the value is a list of <emphasis>unversioned</"
"emphasis> file patterns to be ignored by <command>svn status</command> and "
"other subcommands.  See <xref linkend=\"svn.advanced.props.special.ignore\"/"
">."
msgstr ""
"ディレクトリに設定すると、値は <command>svn status</command> やその他のサブコ"
"マンドで無視される <emphasis>バージョン管理外</emphasis> ファイルのリストで"
"す。<xref linkend=\"svn.advanced.props.special.ignore\"/> をご覧ください。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10989
msgid "<literal>svn:keywords</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:keywords</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:10992
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If present on a file, the value tells the client how to expand particular "
"keywords within the file.  See <xref linkend=\"svn.advanced.props.special."
"keywords\"/>."
msgstr ""
"ファイルに設定すると、この値はクライアントに、ファイルにある特定のキーワード"
"の展開方法を指定します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11002
msgid "<literal>svn:eol-style</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:eol-style</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11005
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If present on a file, the value tells the client how to manipulate the "
"file's line-endings in the working copy and in exported trees.  See <xref "
"linkend=\"svn.advanced.props.special.eol-style\"/> and <xref linkend=\"svn."
"ref.svn.c.export\" /> earlier in this chapter."
msgstr ""
"ファイルに設定すると、この値はクライアントに、作業コピーやエクスポートしたツ"
"リーにある、ファイルの行末の操作方法を指示します。<xref linkend=\"svn."
"advanced.props.special.eol-style\"/> や、この章で前述した <xref linkend="
"\"svn.ref.svn.c.export\"/> をご覧ください。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11015
msgid "<literal>svn:externals</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:externals</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11018
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If present on a directory, the value is a multiline list of other paths and "
"URLs the client should check out.  See <xref linkend=\"svn.advanced.externals"
"\"/>."
msgstr ""
"ディレクトリに設定すると、この値は、クライアントがチェックアウトするべき、他"
"のパスや URL の複数行リストです。<xref linkend=\"svn.advanced.externals\"/> "
"をご覧ください。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11027
msgid "<literal>svn:special</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:special</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><footnote><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11032
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"As of this writing, symbolic links are indeed the only <quote>special</"
"quote> objects.  But there might be more in future releases of Subversion."
msgstr ""
"執筆時点では、シンボリックリンクが唯一の <quote>特殊 (special)</quote> オブ"
"ジェクトです。しかし、Subversion の将来のリリースで、追加される可能性がありま"
"す。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11030
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If present on a file, indicates that the file is not an ordinary file, but a "
"symbolic link or other special object.<placeholder type=\"footnote\" id="
"\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""
"ファイルに設定すると、通常のファイルではなく、シンボリックリンクやその他特殊"
"なオブジェクトであることを示します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11041
msgid "<literal>svn:needs-lock</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:needs-lock</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11044
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If present on a file, tells the client to make the file read-only in the "
"working copy, as a reminder that the file should be locked before editing "
"begins.  See <xref linkend=\"svn.advanced.locking.lock-communication\"/>."
msgstr ""
"ファイルに設定すると、これは、編集が始まる前にファイルがロックされるべきであ"
"ることを告知するのに、作業コピーのファイルを読み込み専用にするよう、クライア"
"ントに指定します。<xref linkend=\"svn.advanced.locking.lock-communication\"/"
"> をご覧ください。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11054
msgid "<literal>svn:mergeinfo</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:mergeinfo</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11057
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Used by Subversion to track merge data.  See <xref linkend=\"svn.branchmerge."
"basicmerging.mergeinfo\"/> for details, but you should never edit this "
"property unless you <emphasis>really</emphasis> know what you're doing."
msgstr ""
"マージデータを追跡するために Subversion が使用します。詳細は <xref linkend="
"\"svn.branchmerge.basicmerging.mergeinfo\"/> をご覧いただきたいのですが、何を"
"しようとしているのか <emphasis>本当に</emphasis> 理解している場合以外は、この"
"属性を編集するべきではありません。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11071
msgid "Unversioned Properties"
msgstr "バージョン管理外の属性"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11073
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "These are the unversioned properties tht Subversion reserves for its own "
#| "use:"
msgid ""
"These are the unversioned properties that Subversion reserves for its own "
"use:"
msgstr ""
"Subversion が使用するため予約している、バージョン管理外の属性は以下の通りで"
"す。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11079
msgid "<literal>svn:author</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:author</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11082
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If present, contains the authenticated username of the person who created "
"the revision.  (If not present, the revision was committed anonymously.)"
msgstr ""
"設定されている場合、そのリビジョンを作成した人の認証ユーザ名が入っています "
"(ない場合、そのリビジョンは匿名でコミットされています)。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11090
msgid "<literal>svn:autoversioned</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:autoversioned</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11093
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If present, the revision was created via the autoversioning feature.  See "
"<xref linkend=\"svn.webdav.autoversioning\"/>."
msgstr ""
"設定されている場合、そのリビジョンは自動バージョン管理機構で作成されたことを"
"表しています。<xref linkend=\"svn.webdav.autoversioning\"/> をご覧ください。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11101
msgid "<literal>svn:date</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:date</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11104
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Contains the UTC time the revision was created, in ISO 8601 format.  The "
"value comes from the <emphasis>server</emphasis> machine's clock, not the "
"client's."
msgstr ""
"そのリビジョンを作成した UTC 時間が (ISO 8601 形式で) 入っています。この値"
"は、<emphasis>サーバ</emphasis> マシンの時計から取得し、クライアントの時計か"
"らではありません。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11113
msgid "<literal>svn:log</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:log</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11116
msgid "Contains the log message describing the revision."
msgstr "そのリビジョンを説明する、ログメッセージが入っています。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11123
msgid "<literal>svn:sync-currently-copying</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:sync-currently-copying</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11126
msgid ""
"Contains the revision number from the source repository which is currently "
"being mirrored to this one by the <command>svnsync</command> tool.  (This "
"property is only relevant when it appears on revision 0.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11135
msgid "<literal>svn:sync-from-uuid</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:sync-from-uuid</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11138
msgid ""
"Contains the UUID of the repository of which this repository has been "
"initialized as a mirror by the <command>svnsync</command> tool.  (This "
"property is only relevant when it appears on revision 0.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11147
msgid "<literal>svn:sync-from-url</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:sync-from-url</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11150
msgid ""
"Contains the URL of the repository directory of which this repository has "
"been initialized as a mirror by the <command>svnsync</command> tool.  (This "
"property is only relevant when it appears on revision 0.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11159
msgid "<literal>svn:sync-last-merged-rev</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:sync-last-merged-rev</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11162
msgid ""
"Contains the revision of the source repository which was most recently and "
"successfully mirrored to this one.  (This property is only relevant when it "
"appears on revision 0.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11171
msgid "<literal>svn:sync-lock</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>svn:sync-lock</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11174
msgid ""
"Used to temporarily enforce mutually exclusive access to the repository by "
"<command>svnsync</command> mirroring operations.  This property is generally "
"only observed when such an operation is active&mdash;or when an "
"<command>svnsync</command> command failed to cleanly disconnect from the "
"repository.  (This property is only relevant when it appears on revision 0.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11195
msgid "Repository Hooks"
msgstr "リポジトリーのフック"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11197
msgid "These are the repository hooks that Subversion provides:"
msgstr "以下は、Subversion が提供しているリポジトリーフックです。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refname>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11205 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11209
msgid "start-commit"
msgstr "start-commit"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refpurpose>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11210
msgid "Notification of the beginning of a commit."
msgstr "コミット開始通知"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11216
msgid ""
"The start-commit hook is run before the commit transaction is even created.  "
"It is typically used to decide whether the user has commit privileges at all."
msgstr ""
"start-commit フックは、コミットトランザクションが作成される直前に実行されま"
"す。通常は、ユーザーにコミット権があるかを判定するのに使用します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11220
msgid ""
"If the start-commit hook program returns a nonzero exit value, the commit is "
"stopped before the commit transaction is even created, and anything printed "
"to <filename>stderr</filename> is marshalled back to the client."
msgstr ""
"start-commit フックプログラムの終了コードが非ゼロの場合、コミットトランザク"
"ションを作成する前にコミットを中止し、出力した <filename>stderr</filename> の"
"内容をクライアントに順次送信します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11228
msgid "Input Parameter(s)"
msgstr "入力パラメータ"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11230 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11297
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11365 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11421
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11497 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11583
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11648 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11709
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11774
msgid "The command-line arguments passed to the hook program, in order, are:"
msgstr "以下のコマンドライン引数が、この順番にフックプログラムに渡されます。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11235 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11302
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11370 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11426
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11502 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11588
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11653 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11714
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11779
msgid "Repository path"
msgstr "リポジトリーのパス"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11238
msgid "Authenticated username attempting the commit"
msgstr "コミットする認証ユーザ名"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11241
msgid ""
"Colon-separated list of capabilities that a client passes to the server, "
"including <literal>depth</literal>, <literal>mergeinfo</literal>, and "
"<literal>log-revprops</literal> (new in Subversion 1.5)."
msgstr ""
"クライアントがサーバーに渡す機能 (<literal>depth</literal>, "
"<literal>mergeinfo</literal>, <literal>log-revprops</literal>) のコロン区切り"
"リスト (Subversion 1.5 の新機能)"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11251 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11323
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11379 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11451
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11526 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11609
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11667 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11735
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11793
msgid "Common uses"
msgstr "典型的な利用方法"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11253
msgid "Access control (e.g., temporarily lock out commits for some reason)."
msgstr "アクセス制御 (何らかの理由で一時的にコミットを禁止するなど)。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11256
msgid ""
"A means to allow access only from clients that have certain capabilities."
msgstr "特定の機能を持つクライアントのみにアクセス許可を出す方法。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refname>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11268 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11272
msgid "pre-commit"
msgstr "pre-commit"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refpurpose>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11273
msgid "Notification just prior to commit completion."
msgstr "コミット実行前通知"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11279
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The <literal>pre-commit</literal> hook is run just before a commit "
"transaction is promoted to a new revision.  Typically, this hook is used to "
"protect against commits that are disallowed due to content or location (e."
"g., your site might require that all commits to a certain branch include a "
"ticket number from the bug tracker, or that the incoming log message is "
"nonempty)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>pre-commit</literal> フックは、新しいリビジョンへコミットトランザク"
"ションを進める前に実行されます。典型的には、コミットの内容や場所 (たとえば、"
"あなたのサイトではすべてのコミットは、バグトラッカのチケット番号を含むブラン"
"チに対してしなくてはならないとか、ログメッセージが空ではいけないなど) によ"
"り、コミットを許可しないようにするために使われます。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11287
msgid ""
"If the <literal>pre-commit</literal> hook program returns a nonzero exit "
"value, the commit is aborted, the commit transaction is removed, and "
"anything printed to <filename>stderr</filename> is marshalled back to the "
"client."
msgstr ""
"<literal>pre-commit</literal> フックプログラムの終了コードが非ゼロの場合、コ"
"ミットを中止し、コミットトランザクションを削除し、出力した <filename>stderr</"
"filename> の内容をクライアントに順次送信します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><title>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11295 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11363
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11419 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11495
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11581 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11646
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11707 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11772
msgid "Input parameter(s)"
msgstr "入力パラメータ"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11305
msgid "Commit transaction name"
msgstr "コミットトランザクション名"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11309
msgid ""
"Additionally, Subversion passes any lock tokens provided by the committing "
"client to the hook script via standard input.  When present, these are "
"formatted as a single line containing the string <literal>LOCK-TOKENS:</"
"literal>, followed by additional lines&mdash;one per lock token&mdash;which "
"contain the lock token information.  Each lock token information line "
"consists of the URI-escaped repository filesystem path associated with the "
"lock, followed by the pipe (<literal>|</literal>) separator character, and "
"finally the lock token string."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11324
msgid "Change validation and control"
msgstr "変更の検証と制御"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refname>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11335 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11339
msgid "post-commit"
msgstr "post-commit"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refpurpose>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11340
msgid "Notification of a successful commit."
msgstr "コミット成功通知"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11346
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The <literal>post-commit</literal> hook is run after the transaction is "
"committed and a new revision is created.  Most people use this hook to send "
"out descriptive emails about the commit or to notify some other tool (such "
"as an issue tracker) that a commit has happened.  Some configurations also "
"use this hook to trigger backup processes."
msgstr ""
"<literal>post-commit</literal> フックは、トランザクションがコミットされ、新し"
"いリビジョンが作られた後に実行されます。ほとんどの人はこのフックを、コミット"
"に関する連絡メールの送信や、コミットの発生を他のツール (課題トラッカなど) に"
"通知するのに使用します。バックアップ処理へのトリガとして、このフックを使用す"
"るという設定もあります。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11353
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If the <literal>post-commit</literal> hook returns a nonzero exit status, "
"the commit <emphasis>will not</emphasis> be aborted since it has already "
"completed.  However, anything that the hook printed to <filename>stderr</"
"filename> will be marshalled back to the client, making it easier to "
"diagnose hook failures."
msgstr ""
"<literal>post-commit</literal> フックの終了ステータスが非ゼロの場合、コミット"
"はすでに完了しているため、中断することは<emphasis>ありません</emphasis>。しか"
"し、フックが <filename>stderr</filename> に出力した内容は、フックのエラーを診"
"断しやすいよう、並べてクライアントに戻ります。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11373
msgid "Revision number created by the commit"
msgstr "コミットで作成したリビジョン番号"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11380
msgid "Commit notification; tool integration"
msgstr "コミット通知、ツール統合"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refname>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11391 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11395
msgid "pre-revprop-change"
msgstr "pre-revprop-change"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refpurpose>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11396
msgid "Notification of a revision property change attempt."
msgstr "リビジョン属性の変更通知"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11403
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The <literal>pre-revprop-change</literal> hook is run immediately prior to "
"the modification of a revision property when performed outside the scope of "
"a normal commit.  Unlike the other hooks, the default state of this one is "
"to deny the proposed action.  The hook must actually exist and return a zero "
"exit value before a revision property modification can happen."
msgstr ""
"<literal>pre-revprop-change</literal> フックは、リビジョン属性の変更が通常の"
"コミットの外側で行われた場合、その変更の直前に実行されます。他のフックと違"
"い、デフォルト状態では実行を拒否します。リビジョン属性の変更が起きる前に、こ"
"のフックが存在しており、終了コードがゼロでなければなりません。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11411
msgid ""
"If the <literal>pre-revprop-change</literal> hook doesn't exist, isn't "
"executable, or returns a nonzero exit value, no change to the property will "
"be made, and anything printed to <filename>stderr</filename> is marshalled "
"back to the client."
msgstr ""
"<literal>pre-revprop-change</literal> フックが存在しない、実行できない、終了"
"コードが非ゼロであった場合、行う予定だった属性の変更は行われず、出力した "
"<filename>stderr</filename> の内容をクライアントに順次送信します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11429
msgid "Revision whose property is about to be modified"
msgstr "属性を変更されたリビジョン"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11432
msgid "Authenticated username attempting the property change"
msgstr "属性を変更する認証ユーザ名"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11435 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11511
msgid "Name of the property changed"
msgstr "変更した属性名"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11438 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11514
msgid ""
"Change description: <literal>A</literal> (added), <literal>D</literal> "
"(deleted), or <literal>M</literal> (modified)"
msgstr ""
"変更種別: <literal>A</literal> (追加), <literal>D</literal> (削除), "
"<literal>M</literal> (変更)"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11444
msgid ""
"Additionally, Subversion passes the intended new value of the property to "
"the hook program via standard input."
msgstr ""
"さらに Subversion は、フックプログラムの標準入力経由で、対象の属性値を渡しま"
"す。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11452
msgid "Access control; change validation and control"
msgstr "アクセス制御、変更の検証と制御"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refname>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11463 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11467
msgid "post-revprop-change"
msgstr "post-revprop-change"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refpurpose>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11468
msgid "Notification of a successful revision property change."
msgstr "リビジョン属性の変更成功通知"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11475
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The <literal>post-revprop-change</literal> hook is run immediately after the "
"modification of a revision property when performed outside the scope of a "
"normal commit.  As you can derive from the description of its counterpart, "
"the <literal>pre-revprop-change</literal> hook, this hook will not run at "
"all unless the <literal>pre-revprop-change</literal> hook is implemented.  "
"It is typically used to send email notification of the property change."
msgstr ""
"<literal>post-revprop-change</literal> フックは、リビジョン属性の変更が通常の"
"コミットの外側で行われた場合、その変更の直後に実行されます。片割れの "
"<literal>pre-revprop-change</literal> フックの説明に由来するように、"
"<literal>pre-revprop-change</literal> フックが実装されていないと、このフック"
"はまったく動作しません。通常、属性変更の通知を email で送信するのに使用しま"
"す。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11485
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If the <literal>post-revprop-change</literal> hook returns a nonzero exit "
"status, the change <emphasis>will not</emphasis> be aborted since it has "
"already completed.  However, anything that the hook printed to "
"<filename>stderr</filename> will be marshalled back to the client, making it "
"easier to diagnose hook failures."
msgstr ""
"<literal>post-revprop-change</literal> フックの終了ステータスが非ゼロの場合、"
"変更ははすでに完了しているため、中断することは<emphasis>ありません</"
"emphasis>。しかし、フックが <filename>stderr</filename> に出力した内容は、"
"フックのエラーを診断しやすいよう、並べてクライアントに戻ります。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11505
msgid "Revision whose property was modified"
msgstr "属性が変更されたリビジョン"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11508
msgid "Authenticated username of the person making the change"
msgstr "変更を行う認証ユーザ名"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11520
msgid ""
"Additionally, Subversion passes to the hook program, via standard input, the "
"previous value of the property."
msgstr ""
"さらに Subversion は、フックプログラムの標準入力経由で、属性の以前の値を渡し"
"ます。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11527
msgid "Property change notification"
msgstr "属性変更通知"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refname>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11538 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11542
msgid "pre-lock"
msgstr "pre-lock"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refpurpose>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11543
msgid "Notification of a path lock attempt."
msgstr "パスのロック取得通知"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11549
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The <literal>pre-lock</literal> hook runs whenever someone attempts to lock "
"a path.  It can be used to prevent locks altogether or to create a more "
"complex policy specifying exactly which users are allowed to lock particular "
"paths.  If the hook notices a preexisting lock, it can also decide whether a "
"user is allowed to <quote>steal</quote> the existing lock."
msgstr ""
"<literal>pre-lock</literal> フックは、誰かがパスをロックしようとしたときに、"
"常に実行されます。これはロックを防ぐのに利用できますし、どのユーザが特定のパ"
"スに対してロックできるか、といった複雑なポリシーを設定するのにも使えます。"
"フックが既存のロックに気づいた場合、ユーザが既存のロックを <quote>奪える</"
"quote> かどうか、決めることもできます。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11557
msgid ""
"If the <literal>pre-lock</literal> hook program returns a nonzero exit "
"value, the lock action is aborted and anything printed to <filename>stderr</"
"filename> is marshalled back to the client."
msgstr ""
"<literal>pre-lock</literal> フックプログラムの終了コードが非ゼロであった場"
"合、ロック処理を中止し、出力した <filename>stderr</filename> の内容をクライア"
"ントに順次送信します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11562
msgid ""
"The hook program may optionally dictate the lock token which will be "
"assigned to the lock by printing the desired lock token to standard output.  "
"Because of this, implementations of this hook should carefully avoid "
"unexpected output sent to standard output."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><warning><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11569
msgid ""
"If the <literal>pre-lock</literal> script takes advantage of lock token "
"dictation feature, the responsibility of generating a <emphasis>unique</"
"emphasis> lock token falls to the script itself.  Failure to generate unique "
"lock tokens may result in undefined&mdash;and very likely, undesired&mdash;"
"behavior."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11591
msgid "Versioned path that is to be locked"
msgstr "ロックを行うバージョン管理下のパス"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11594
msgid "Authenticated username of the person attempting the lock"
msgstr "ロックを取得する認証ユーザ名"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11598
msgid "Comment provided when the lock was created"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11601
msgid ""
"<literal>1</literal> if the user is attempting to steal an existing lock; "
"<literal>0</literal> otherwise"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11610 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11736
msgid "Access control"
msgstr "アクセス制御"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refname>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11621 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11625
msgid "post-lock"
msgstr "post-lock"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refpurpose>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11626
msgid "Notification of a successful path lock."
msgstr "パスのロック取得成功通知"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11632
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The <literal>post-lock</literal> hook runs after one or more paths have been "
"locked.  It is typically used to send email notification of the lock event."
msgstr ""
"<literal>post-lock</literal> フックは、ひとつ以上のパスのロックが行われると実"
"行されます。通常、ロックイベントの通知で email を送信するのに使用します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11636
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If the <literal>post-lock</literal> hook returns a nonzero exit status, the "
"lock <emphasis>will not</emphasis> be aborted since it has already "
"completed.  However, anything that the hook printed to <filename>stderr</"
"filename> will be marshalled back to the client, making it easier to "
"diagnose hook failures."
msgstr ""
"<literal>post-lock</literal> フックの終了ステータスが非ゼロの場合、ロックはす"
"でに完了しているため、中断することは<emphasis>ありません</emphasis>。しかし、"
"フックが <filename>stderr</filename> に出力した内容は、フックのエラーを診断し"
"やすいよう、並べてクライアントに戻ります。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11656
msgid "Authenticated username of the person who locked the paths"
msgstr "パスをロックしたユーザの認証ユーザ名"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11661
msgid ""
"Additionally, the list of paths locked is passed to the hook program via "
"standard input, one path per line."
msgstr ""
"さらに、フックプログラムの標準入力経由で、ロックしたパスのリストを渡します。"
"1 行につき 1 パスです。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11668
msgid "Lock notification"
msgstr "ロック取得通知"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refname>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11679 en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11683
msgid "pre-unlock"
msgstr "pre-unlock"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refnamediv><refpurpose>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11684
msgid "Notification of a path unlock attempt."
msgstr "パスのロック解除通知"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11690
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The <literal>pre-unlock</literal> hook runs whenever someone attempts to "
"remove a lock on a file.  It can be used to create policies that specify "
"which users are allowed to unlock particular paths.  It's particularly "
"important for determining policies about lock breakage.  If user A locks a "
"file, is user B allowed to break the lock? What if the lock is more than a "
"week old? These sorts of things can be decided and enforced by the hook."
msgstr ""
"<literal>pre-unlock</literal> フックは、誰かがファイルのロックを解除しようと"
"した時に、常に実行されます。これを使えば、どのユーザが、どの特定のパスに対し"
"てロックを解除できるかといった、ポリシーを作るために利用できます。ロック解除"
"に関するポリシーを決めることは非常に重要です。ユーザ A がファイルをロックした"
"場合、B はそのロックを解除できるのでしょうか? ロックが一週間以上も前のもの"
"だった場合は? これらのことはフックにより決定し、強制できます。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11699
msgid ""
"If the <literal>pre-unlock</literal> hook program returns a nonzero exit "
"value, the unlock action is aborted and anything printed to "
"<filename>stderr</filename> is marshalled back to the client."
msgstr ""
"<literal>pre-unlock</literal> フックプログラムの終了コードが非ゼロであった場"
"合、ロック解除処理を中止し、出力した <filename>stderr</filename> の内容をクラ"
"イアントに順次送信します。"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11717
msgid "Versioned path which is to be unlocked"
msgstr "ロック解除するバージョン管理下のパス"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11720
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Authenticated username of the person attempting the lock"
msgid "Authenticated username of the person attempting the unlock"
msgstr "ロックを取得する認証ユーザ名"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/book/ch09-reference.xml:11724
